        <div type="textpart" n="5" xml:id="part5">
          <head>Liber V</head>
          <!--Each new major section (e.g., book, volume) has a new <div>.-->
          <p>
            <seg n="1"><milestone unit="page" n="58" edRef="#Tiguri1558"/><milestone unit="page"
                n="216" edRef="#Basileae1568 #Argentinae1590"/><milestone unit="page" n="57"
                edRef="#Lugduni1559"/>Mane cum gravatim a somno surgis, in <app>
                <lem wit="#Tiguri1558 #Lugduni1559">promptu</lem>
                <rdg wit="#Basileae1568 #Argentinae1590">promtu</rdg>
              </app> tibi sit cogitare, te ad humanum opus faciendum surgere.</seg>
            <seg n="2">Itaque ergo (dices) gravate accedo ad agenda ea, quorum causa natus sum,
                <milestone unit="page" n="58" edRef="#Lugduni1559"/>ac <app>
                <lem wit="#Lugduni1559 #Basileae1568 #Argentinae1590">propter</lem>
                <rdg wit="#Tiguri1558">proter</rdg>
              </app> quae in hunc veni mundum?</seg>
            <seg n="3">Scilicet in hoc <app>
                <lem>factus</lem>
                <note><ref target="#Casaubon1643">Casaubon</ref>: factus sum</note>
              </app>, ut decumbens in lecto meipsum calefaciam?</seg>
            <seg n="4">Atqui hoc iucundius est.</seg>
            <seg n="5">Ergone ad voluptatem natus es, non ad <app>
                <lem>agendum</lem>
                <note><ref target="#Casaubon1643">Casaubon</ref>: agendum et operandum</note>
              </app>?</seg>
            <seg n="6">Non vides plantulas, passerculos, formicas, <app>
                <lem wit="#Lugduni1559 #Basileae1568 #Argentinae1590">araneas</lem>
                <rdg wit="#Tiguri1558">arcaneas</rdg>
              </app>, apes, singula haec suo intenta <app>
                <lem>officio</lem>
                <note><ref target="#Casaubon1643">Casaubon</ref>: officio proprii mundi cursum
                  officiumque consummare?</note>
              </app>?</seg>
            <seg n="7">Tu vero ea quae sunt hominis obire recusas, neque <app>
                <lem>ad id te confers</lem>
                <note><ref target="#Casaubon1643">Casaubon</ref>: ad id properas</note>
              </app> quod naturae tuae convenit?</seg>
            <seg n="8">At vero quiete opus est.</seg>
            <seg n="9">Sane, sed et huic modum statuit natura, perinde ut edendi bibendique.</seg>
            <seg n="10">Atqui tu ultra modum, <app>
                <lem wit="#Basileae1568">et id quod</lem>
                <rdg wit="#Tiguri1558">iam qui quod</rdg>
                <rdg wit="#Lugduni1559">iam id quod</rdg>
                <note><ref target="#Casaubon1643">Casuabon</ref>: et id quod</note>
              </app> satis est, procedis:</seg>
            <seg n="11">in rebus vero agendis <app>
                <lem wit="#Lugduni1559 #Basileae1568 #Argentinae1590">intra</lem>
                <rdg wit="#Tiguri1558">intro</rdg>
              </app> modum subsistis.</seg>
            <seg n="12">Fit hoc eo, quia teipsum non diligis.</seg>
            <seg n="13">Alioquin enim et <milestone unit="page" n="59" edRef="#Tiguri1558"/>naturam
                <milestone unit="page" n="217" edRef="#Basileae1568 #Argentinae1590"/>tuam eiusque
              voluntatem diligeres.</seg>
            <seg n="14">Etenim alii qui suas <app><lem wit="#Tiguri1558 #Lugduni1559">artes</lem><rdg wit="#Basileae1568 #Argentinae1590">arres</rdg></app> amant, operibus suis ita incumbunt, ut neque balneorum
              neque cibi curam habeant</seg>
            <seg n="16">Hi enim quarum rerum studio tenentur, dum eas <app>
                <lem>augere</lem>
                <note>NOTE HERE</note>
              </app> possint, cibum et somnum postponunt.</seg>
          </p>
